ington Poststated, \\\"It remains unclear what standards Khelif andLin Yu-tingfailed [in 2023] to lead to the disqualifications\\\",[39][38]adding \\\"There never has been evidence that [...] Khelif [...] had XY chromosomes or elevated levels of testosterone.\", \"from\": 5190, \"to\": 5456, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Washington\", \"from\": 5202, \"to\": 5212}, {\"ngram\": \"Khelif\", \"from\": 5260, \"to\": 5266}, {\"ngram\": \"the disqualifications\\\",[39][38]adding\", \"from\": 5309, \"to\": 5346}, {\"ngram\": \"evidence\", \"from\": 5369, \"to\": 5377}, {\"ngram\": \"[...] Khelif\", \"from\": 5383, \"to\": 5395}, {\"ngram\": \"XY chromosomes\", \"from\": 5406, \"to\": 5420}, {\"ngram\": \"elevated levels\", \"from\": 5424, \"to\": 5439}, {\"ngram\": \"testosterone\", \"from\": 5443, \"to\": 5455}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"[39]The IBA did not reveal the testing methodology, stating the \\\"specifics remain confidential\\\".\", \"from\": 5456, \"to\": 5553, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5465, \"end\": 5468, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Independent_Broadcasting_Authority\", \"score\": 0.9999999999663487, \"rank\": 3.375888511629139e-11, \"text\": \"IBA\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Independent_Broadcasting_Authority\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Independent_Broadcasting_Authority\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the testing methodology\", \"from\": 5484, \"to\": 5507}, {\"ngram\": \"the \\\"specifics\", \"from\": 5517, \"to\": 5531}]}, {\"sentence\": \"[40]At the time, Khelif said the ruling meant having \\\"characteristics that mean I can not box with women\\\", but said she was the victim of a \\\"big conspiracy\\\" regarding the disqualification.\", \"from\": 5553, \"to\": 5741, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Khelif\", \"from\": 5570, \"to\": 5576}, {\"ngram\": \"the ruling\", \"from\": 5582, \"to\": 5592}, {\"ngram\": \"characteristics\", \"from\": 5607, \"to\": 5622}, {\"ngram\": \"women\", \"from\": 5652, \"to\": 5657}, {\"ngram\": \"the victim\", \"from\": 5677, \"to\": 5687}, {\"ngram\": \"a \\\"big conspiracy\", \"from\": 5691, \"to\": 5708}, {\"ngram\": \"the disqualification\", \"from\": 5720, \"to\": 5740}]}, {\"sentence\": \"[41]She initially appealed to theCourt of Arbitration for Sportbut the appeal was terminated since Khelif could not pay the procedural costs.\", \"from\": 5741, \"to\": 5882, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"theCourt\", \"from\": 5771, \"to\": 5779}, {\"ngram\": \"Arbitration\", \"from\": 5783, \"to\": 5794}, {\"ngram\": \"Sportbut\", \"from\": 5799, \"to\": 5807}, {\"ngram\": \"the appeal\", \"from\": 5808, \"to\": 5818}, {\"ngram\": \"Khelif\", \"from\": 5840, \"to\": 5846}, {\"ngram\": \"the procedural costs\", \"from\": 5861, \"to\": 5881}]}, {\"sentence\": \"[42][43] In late July 2024, both Lin and Khelif were officially deemed eligible to compete at the2024 Summer Olympic Gamesby theInternational Olympic Committee(IOC).\", \"from\": 5882, \"to\": 6048, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"late July\", \"from\": 5894, \"to\": 5903}, {\"ngram\": \"both Lin\", \"from\": 5910, \"to\": 5918}, {\"ngram\": \"Khelif\", \"from\": 5923, \"to\": 5929}, {\"ngram\": \"the2024 Summer Olympic Gamesby\", \"from\": 5976, \"to\": 6006}, {\"ngram\": \"theInternational Olympic Committee(IOC\", \"from\": 6007, \"to\": 6045}]}, {\"sentence\": \"[44]In a statement, the IOC said \\\"All athletes participating in the boxing tournament of the Olympic Games Paris 2024 comply with the competition's eligibility and entry regulations, as well as all applicable medical regulations in accordance with rules 1.4 and 3.1 of the Paris 2024 Boxing Unit.\", \"from\": 6048, \"to\": 6344, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6072, \"end\": 6075, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.4522877078836602e-60, \"text\": \"IOC\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}, {\"begin\": 6332, \"end\": 6338, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Boxing\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.006710175466401e-25, \"text\": \"Boxing\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Boxing\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Boxing\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"All athletes\", \"from\": 6082, \"to\": 6094}, {\"ngram\": \"the boxing tournament\", \"from\": 6112, \"to\": 6133}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympic Games Paris\", \"from\": 6137, \"to\": 6160}, {\"ngram\": \"the competition's eligibility and entry regulations\", \"from\": 6178, \"to\": 6229}, {\"ngram\": \"accordance\", \"from\": 6280, \"to\": 6290}, {\"ngram\": \"rules\", \"from\": 6296, \"to\": 6301}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"[44] The announcement attracted widespread attention and criticism online.\", \"from\": 6344, \"to\": 6420, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The announcement\", \"from\": 6350, \"to\": 6366}, {\"ngram\": \"widespread attention\", \"from\": 6377, \"to\": 6397}, {\"ngram\": \"criticism\", \"from\": 6402, \"to\": 6411}]}, {\"sentence\": \"[45][46]Shortly after the IOC's announcement, theInternational Boxing Association(IBA) issued a statement criticising the decision, citing concerns around the IOC's handling of competitive fairness and athlete safety.\", \"from\": 6420, \"to\": 6637, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6446, \"end\": 6449, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.4522877078836602e-60, \"text\": \"IOC\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}, {\"begin\": 6579, \"end\": 6582, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.4522877078836602e-60, \"text\": \"IOC\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"theInternational Boxing Association(IBA\", \"from\": 6466, \"to\": 6505}, {\"ngram\": \"a statement\", \"from\": 6514, \"to\": 6525}, {\"ngram\": \"the decision\", \"from\": 6538, \"to\": 6550}, {\"ngram\": \"concerns\", \"from\": 6559, \"to\": 6567}, {\"ngram\": \"competitive fairness\", \"from\": 6597, \"to\": 6617}, {\"ngram\": \"athlete safety\", \"from\": 6622, \"to\": 6636}]}, {\"sentence\": \"[47]The IBA reaffirmed its March 2023 decision to disqualify Lin and Khelif from the2023 Women's World Boxing Championships, citing the athletes' failure to meet the eligibility criteria for women's competition.\", \"from\": 6637, \"to\": 6848, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6645, \"end\": 6648, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Independent_Broadcasting_Authority\", \"score\": 0.9999999999663487, \"rank\": 3.375888511629139e-11, \"text\": \"IBA\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Independent_Broadcasting_Authority\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Independent_Broadcasting_Authority\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"its March 2023 decision\", \"from\": 6660, \"to\": 6683}, {\"ngram\": \"Lin\", \"from\": 6698, \"to\": 6701}, {\"ngram\": \"Khelif\", \"from\": 6706, \"to\": 6712}, {\"ngram\": \"the2023\", \"from\": 6718, \"to\": 6725}, {\"ngram\": \"Women's World Boxing Championships\", \"from\": 6726, \"to\": 6760}, {\"ngram\": \"the athletes' failure\", \"from\": 6769, \"to\": 6790}, {\"ngram\": \"the eligibility criteria\", \"from\": 6799, \"to\": 6823}, {\"ngram\": \"women's competition\", \"from\": 6828, \"to\": 6847}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The IBA clarified that Khelif and Lin \\\"did not undergo a testosterone examination but were subject to a separate and recognized test, whereby the specifics remain confidential\\\", and further alleged that they \\\"were found to have competitive advantages over other female competitors\\\".\", \"from\": 6849, \"to\": 7131, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6853, \"end\": 6856, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Independent_Broadcasting_Authority\", \"score\": 0.9999999999663487, \"rank\": 3.375888511629139e-11, \"text\": \"IBA\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Independent_Broadcasting_Authority\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Independent_Broadcasting_Authority\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Khelif\", \"from\": 6872, \"to\": 6878}, {\"ngram\": \"Lin\", \"from\": 6883, \"to\": 6886}, {\"ngram\": \"a testosterone examination\", \"from\": 6904, \"to\": 6930}, {\"ngram\": \"a separate and recognized test\", \"from\": 6951, \"to\": 6981}, {\"ngram\": \"the specifics\", \"from\": 6991, \"to\": 7004}, {\"ngram\": \"competitive advantages\", \"from\": 7077, \"to\": 7099}, {\"ngram\": \"other female competitors\", \"from\": 7105, \"to\": 7129}]}, {\"sentence\": \"[48][better source needed] The following day, the IOC released their own statement in response, stating that the IBA's decision was \\\"sudden and arbitrary\\\" and \\\"without any due process\\\".\", \"from\": 7131, \"to\": 7317, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7182, \"end\": 7185, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.4522877078836602e-60, \"text\": \"IOC\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}, {\"begin\": 7245, \"end\": 7248, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Independent_Broadcasting_Authority\", \"score\": 0.9999999999663487, \"rank\": 3.375888511629139e-11, \"text\": \"IBA\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Independent_Broadcasting_Authority\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Independent_Broadcasting_Authority\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"48][better source\", \"from\": 7132, \"to\": 7149}, {\"ngram\": \"their own statement\", \"from\": 7194, \"to\": 7213}, {\"ngram\": \"response\", \"from\": 7217, \"to\": 7225}, {\"ngram\": \"any due process\", \"from\": 7299, \"to\": 7314}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The IOC further stated: According to the IBA minutes available on their website, this decision was initially taken solely by the IBA Secretary General and CEO.\", \"from\": 7318, \"to\": 7478, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7322, \"end\": 7325, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.4522877078836602e-60, \"text\": \"IOC\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}, {\"begin\": 7360, \"end\": 7363, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Independent_Broadcasting_Authority\", \"score\": 0.9999999999663487, \"rank\": 3.375888511629139e-11, \"text\": \"IBA\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Independent_Broadcasting_Authority\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Independent_Broadcasting_Authority\"}, {\"begin\": 7448, \"end\": 7451, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Independent_Broadcasting_Authority\", \"score\": 0.9999999999663487, \"rank\": 3.375888511629139e-11, \"text\": \"IBA\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Independent_Broadcasting_Authority\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Independent_Broadcasting_Authority\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"their website\", \"from\": 7384, \"to\": 7397}, {\"ngram\": \"this deci